Centrica Plc (CNA) , the U.K.â€™s biggest
residential gas supplier, signed a 500 million-pound ($793
million) 364-day revolving credit facility last week, according
to an e-mail from lenders.  Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ Ltd. led the deal as agent,
and was joined by mandated lead arrangers Credit Suisse Group
AG, Goldman Sachs Group Inc., Royal Bank of Canada and UBS AG,
Bank of Tokyo said in the e-mail. The loan has the option of
being extended for one year, the bank said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
